WEBVTT

01:36.471 --> 01:39.348
<i>The "perpetuity" in the Rules
is just a front.</i>

01:39.349 --> 01:42.018
<i>A smokescreen for the real plan.</i>

01:42.519 --> 01:44.103
<i>I'm certain of it.</i>

01:44.604 --> 01:46.730
<i>When only the strong remain,</i>

01:46.731 --> 01:49.024
<i>Kenjaku will drop a bomb,</i>

01:49.025 --> 01:52.153
<i>and then the Culling Game
will have served its purpose.</i>

01:52.737 --> 01:56.365
<i>We don't know what that bomb is.</i>

01:56.366 --> 01:59.952
<i>And its detonation won't be far off.</i>

01:59.953 --> 02:02.122
It could be right now.

02:02.747 --> 02:06.500
That's why we gather strong allies

02:06.501 --> 02:08.419
and stockpile points in preparation.

02:09.003 --> 02:10.755
There are a few things I want to ask.

02:12.006 --> 02:14.508
I don't think she's that strong.

02:14.509 --> 02:19.596
She is bait. She lures players here
with whatever excuse works.

02:19.597 --> 02:22.183
Women draw less suspicion.

02:23.268 --> 02:26.563
And when she's no use,
you kill her and turn her into points.

02:28.398 --> 02:29.898
What are you talking about?

02:29.899 --> 02:31.651
That's not true.

02:32.777 --> 02:36.029
Mr. Reggie is my true knight.

02:36.030 --> 02:39.200
As long as I serve him, he'll protect me!

02:39.701 --> 02:41.369
You're delusional.

02:41.870 --> 02:45.373
You and your allies together
make 100 points, right?

02:46.916 --> 02:48.126
That's about right.

02:49.043 --> 02:50.503
A new rule is being added soon.

02:51.379 --> 02:54.132
It will allow point transfers
between players.

02:55.800 --> 02:56.759
Hand over

02:57.969 --> 02:59.344
all your points.

02:59.345 --> 03:01.890
Negotiations have broken down…

03:07.186 --> 03:08.187
<i>What?</i>

03:10.940 --> 03:12.107
Hey!

03:12.108 --> 03:13.276
Nue!

03:17.739 --> 03:20.033
Don't ever show me that face again.

03:25.538 --> 03:27.540
Oh, I see…

03:28.291 --> 03:31.710
Thought you were soft.
I guess you can't kill her.

03:31.711 --> 03:34.838
You want our points, right?

03:34.839 --> 03:36.090
But…

03:36.799 --> 03:38.927
if you're not ready to kill,

03:39.427 --> 03:42.305
you'll regret it once you're dead.

04:06.621 --> 04:07.746
Hey!

04:07.747 --> 04:09.539
I'm still here, you know?

04:09.540 --> 04:10.540
IORI HAZENOKI
POINTS OWNED-35

04:10.541 --> 04:11.668
Did he die?

04:20.260 --> 04:21.469
Are you sure?

04:23.137 --> 04:23.846
GASOLINE RECEIPTS

04:24.639 --> 04:26.015
<i>That smell!</i>

04:40.196 --> 04:41.113
Done already?

04:41.114 --> 04:41.864
REGGIE STAR
POINTS OWNED-41

04:42.699 --> 04:45.242
Not yet. Like you,

04:45.243 --> 04:47.996
he ducked into the room
right before the blast.

04:49.539 --> 04:51.498
He's good…

04:51.499 --> 04:54.085
But I bet we shaved off a decent chunk.

05:01.843 --> 05:03.344
You see now, right?

05:04.220 --> 05:06.806
They've got no intention
of protecting you.

05:09.684 --> 05:12.478
If you get it, then get lost!

05:20.236 --> 05:21.904
Give it a rest.

05:22.989 --> 05:25.742
Then say it!

05:27.285 --> 05:29.828
Mr. Reggie said it!

05:29.829 --> 05:31.830
Say you'll protect me!

05:31.831 --> 05:33.915
Say you like me!

05:33.916 --> 05:35.752
Say it!

05:41.424 --> 05:43.092
There are people like you.

05:43.885 --> 05:46.095
Trash who thinks words

05:46.846 --> 05:49.390
matter more than actions.

05:49.891 --> 05:52.101
Hey, thanks for earlier…

05:53.144 --> 05:54.686
But man, you're wrecked.

05:54.687 --> 05:55.645
CHIZURU HARI
POINTS OWNED-28

05:55.646 --> 05:58.023
Climbing back up here
is not easy, you know.

05:58.024 --> 06:00.567
Use the stairs, caveman.

06:00.568 --> 06:03.904
Ring-ring!

06:03.905 --> 06:07.032
A rule has been added

06:07.033 --> 06:08.533
to the Culling Game by a player.

06:08.534 --> 06:09.201
PLAYERS MAY VIEW OTHERS' NAMES, POINTS,
NUMBER OF RULE ADDITIONS, AND COLONY

06:09.202 --> 06:09.785
RULE TEN-A PLAYER MAY TRANSFER
ANY NUMBER OF POINTS TO ANOTHER PLAYER

06:09.786 --> 06:10.827
<i>Rule ten.</i>

06:10.828 --> 06:13.747
<i>Players may transfer</i>

06:13.748 --> 06:15.875
any number of points to other players.

06:16.375 --> 06:18.920
What the hell is this rule?

06:51.911 --> 06:52.995
Max Elephant!

06:56.290 --> 06:57.542
Again?

07:11.305 --> 07:13.850
Damn you!

07:20.273 --> 07:22.859
<i>What am I… doing?</i>

07:24.026 --> 07:25.945
<i>We'll still need points going forward.</i>

07:26.446 --> 07:30.199
<i>But Tsumiki won't be forced
to kill anyone anymore.</i>

07:30.700 --> 07:33.535
<i>Don't rush it. Trust everyone.</i>

07:33.536 --> 07:35.663
<i>Don't obsess over their points.</i>

07:36.456 --> 07:38.124
<i>I just have to give it everything</i>

07:38.708 --> 07:41.169
<i>and brush off what comes my way.</i>

07:41.752 --> 07:44.046
Five points have been added.

07:45.756 --> 07:48.133
What a waste of points.

07:48.134 --> 07:51.804
Getting killed before you even use
your technique is pathetic.

07:53.848 --> 07:55.724
<i>Did Remi retire?</i>

07:55.725 --> 07:57.851
<i>Even if she did, it's two on one.</i>

07:57.852 --> 08:01.062
<i>Damn it. That first bombing
really did a number on me.</i>

08:01.063 --> 08:02.356
<i>Running is not an option…</i>

08:04.358 --> 08:07.028
<i>Should I use… my domain?</i>

08:07.695 --> 08:10.155
<i>But my domain is incomplete.</i>

08:10.156 --> 08:13.159
<i>I can't seal the barrier shut
and trap them inside.</i>

08:14.202 --> 08:15.535
<i>If they escape and I blow it,</i>

08:15.536 --> 08:18.623
<i>a rematch is the worst-case scenario.</i>

08:22.376 --> 08:23.710
That was…

08:23.711 --> 08:29.717
close!

08:33.804 --> 08:35.264
Two on one…

08:36.599 --> 08:39.685
You really think…

08:40.478 --> 08:41.979
that's a fair split?

08:43.272 --> 08:46.317
You know what people call guys like you?

08:47.485 --> 08:50.320
Right. Cowards.

08:50.321 --> 08:53.323
A coward's attack doesn't work.

08:53.324 --> 08:54.784
Look!

08:56.452 --> 08:59.956
Damage zero!

09:47.003 --> 09:48.211
FUMIHIKO TAKABA
POINTS OWNED-0

09:48.212 --> 09:50.380
Kid, I'll back you up.

09:50.381 --> 09:52.424
I'm 35.

09:52.425 --> 09:55.928
One look at someone's face,
and I can tell if they're bad.

09:58.764 --> 10:00.015
What is this?

10:00.016 --> 10:03.435
You've got a pretty nasty face too!

10:03.436 --> 10:04.270
<i>What?</i>

10:04.770 --> 10:05.605
Whatever.

10:06.105 --> 10:08.565
It's relative grading. <i>Yutori</i>.

10:08.566 --> 10:10.192
Isn't <i>Yutori</i> about absolute grading?

10:11.027 --> 10:12.861
<i>He covered for me.</i>

10:12.862 --> 10:15.323
<i>For now, I can trust him, right?</i>

10:16.240 --> 10:18.491
What do you think, Hazenoki?

10:18.492 --> 10:21.703
Never seen him. Faster to just ask.

10:21.704 --> 10:23.204
Hey!

10:23.205 --> 10:24.999
Which side are you on?

10:30.713 --> 10:32.005
I see…

10:32.006 --> 10:33.883
So you're asking…

10:34.675 --> 10:36.051
if I'm funny…

10:36.052 --> 10:39.680
or not… right?

10:40.973 --> 10:43.308
No. What era are you from--

10:43.309 --> 10:46.436
This costume is based on a hero

10:46.437 --> 10:51.191
who taught me
what "laughing hard" really means.

10:51.192 --> 10:52.817
So I can't mess up a joke

10:52.818 --> 10:54.945
in this thing!

10:55.446 --> 10:58.448
<i>Here's a gag I just came up with.</i>

10:58.449 --> 11:01.159
<i>Use it in front of the girl you like.</i>

11:01.160 --> 11:01.827
CURSED

11:04.413 --> 11:05.456
Something is coming.

11:13.339 --> 11:16.133
Mind your own Wi-Fi!

11:25.434 --> 11:27.811
You lousy audience!

11:27.812 --> 11:29.604
Sometimes, there are guys like you!

11:29.605 --> 11:32.690
You forgot how to smile,

11:32.691 --> 11:35.860
yet you sit front row at a show!

11:35.861 --> 11:37.488
<i>That's your problem.</i>

11:38.072 --> 11:39.072
But I…

11:39.073 --> 11:40.490
<i>He reminds me of him.</i>

11:40.491 --> 11:42.284
Even so, I won't abandon you!

11:43.661 --> 11:45.204
Because I'm…

11:47.456 --> 11:48.833
<i>a comedian…</i>

11:55.464 --> 11:58.508
<i>He's fast. His cursed energy spiked fast.</i>

11:58.509 --> 12:00.593
<i>The output is swinging wildly.</i>

12:00.594 --> 12:03.764
- <i>This guy… He's strong…</i>
- Be careful.

12:04.348 --> 12:06.850
I'm an old-school comedian

12:06.851 --> 12:09.270
who is pro-violence.

12:10.354 --> 12:12.648
So, what will you do, kid?

12:17.778 --> 12:20.196
- I'm splitting them up.
- Yes.

12:20.197 --> 12:23.951
Hazenoki's technique probably turns
parts of his body into bombs.

12:24.452 --> 12:27.287
- Also, using reverse cursed technique…
- Yes.

12:27.288 --> 12:28.205
- Too close!
- Yes.

12:28.789 --> 12:30.791
- Kogane!
- Aye!

12:31.459 --> 12:33.419
Pull up Hiromi Higuruma's info!

12:34.420 --> 12:36.171
<i>It was Itadori who added the rule…</i>

12:36.172 --> 12:37.840
HIROMI HIGURUMA-100 POINTS
TOKYO COLONY

12:38.549 --> 12:40.718
I'm done with this colony.

12:42.178 --> 12:43.596
If you back off, I'll let you go.

12:44.930 --> 12:46.473
What?

12:46.474 --> 12:48.391
Who are you to say that?

12:48.392 --> 12:52.312
I'm collecting the points
from Hari, whom you killed.

12:52.313 --> 12:54.523
- You.
- I'm Takaba!

12:55.983 --> 12:58.444
If you're going to kill that bomb guy,

12:59.028 --> 12:59.987
do it, if you can.

13:00.488 --> 13:02.656
But first, take his points.

13:04.533 --> 13:05.659
Okay, kid.

13:06.327 --> 13:08.913
I've heard your request loud and clear.

13:13.959 --> 13:15.544
But I'm a comedian.

13:16.712 --> 13:19.548
I won't do something
that steals someone's smile forever!

13:20.132 --> 13:22.009
Do anything as long as you win.

13:37.107 --> 13:39.026
That's a dangerous technique.

13:40.236 --> 13:41.403
Fire in the hole!

13:41.946 --> 13:43.364
However!

13:43.948 --> 13:45.741
In variety TV…

13:50.371 --> 13:51.622
He's gone…

13:53.916 --> 13:55.501
Red is off-limits, buddy!

14:01.006 --> 14:01.924
<i>Don't mess with me!</i>

14:08.597 --> 14:11.016
Glad Takaba wasn't an enemy.

14:11.517 --> 14:14.395
That's a line I've always wanted to hear!

14:16.146 --> 14:18.440
See you, kid. Don't die!

14:21.360 --> 14:23.444
He died, didn't he?

14:23.445 --> 14:26.948
Getting mocked like that
will make Hazenoki get serious.

14:26.949 --> 14:30.410
Worry about yourself. I told you, right?

14:30.411 --> 14:33.580
I've already achieved my goal
in this colony.

14:33.581 --> 14:36.876
I can fight for real now. No holding back.

15:17.917 --> 15:19.126
Max Elephant!

15:25.174 --> 15:27.593
So, you've got that too?

16:52.761 --> 16:56.139
You've figured out my technique.

16:56.140 --> 16:59.143
But drowning me
is a bit too obvious, isn't it?

17:04.857 --> 17:07.400
Materializing what's on receipts…

17:07.401 --> 17:09.861
Strictly speaking, that's not it, but…

17:09.862 --> 17:11.320
That's right.

17:11.321 --> 17:13.322
It's hard to put into words, but…

17:13.323 --> 17:16.242
it's more like "recreating contracts."

17:16.243 --> 17:18.995
Meaning I can do this too.

17:18.996 --> 17:21.414
Contractual Re-Creation!

17:21.415 --> 17:22.416
RECEIPT
HOSHIZORA TEI

17:26.003 --> 17:27.754
What I just used

17:27.755 --> 17:30.256
<i>was a receipt for a five-star inn,
Hoshizora Tei.</i>

17:30.257 --> 17:33.509
<i>Two nights, three days,</i>

17:33.510 --> 17:35.386
<i>with an oil treatment included.</i>

17:35.387 --> 17:40.433
So right now, I'll be soaking
in a hot spring real slow, loosening up,

17:40.434 --> 17:45.438
then getting two solid days
of good sleep and rest.

17:45.439 --> 17:47.982
Compared to you, how about you?

17:47.983 --> 17:50.193
You're hurt from the last fight,

17:50.194 --> 17:54.448
using multiple <i>shikigami,</i>
and you're exhausted, right?

17:55.115 --> 17:57.450
<i>I use multiple</i> shikigami <i>at once,
all the time.</i>

17:57.451 --> 17:59.243
<i>The problem is that Max Elephant</i>

17:59.244 --> 18:02.456
<i>is in that mix,
while it is meant to be used alone.</i>

18:03.916 --> 18:07.710
You summon and dismiss <i>shikigami</i> fast,

18:07.711 --> 18:11.714
but once one has been damaged,
it doesn't work like that, right?

18:11.715 --> 18:15.259
You can't bring out the dog
that can run, attack, and defend.

18:15.260 --> 18:16.219
So you're stuck

18:16.220 --> 18:19.932
combining single trick <i>shikigami.</i>

18:20.432 --> 18:25.019
Neither of us has some big move
to finish this match.

18:25.020 --> 18:26.479
You're done.

18:26.480 --> 18:28.774
No way you can kill me.

18:30.818 --> 18:33.445
You're right. So I'm going to run.

18:34.029 --> 18:34.988
What?

18:43.956 --> 18:45.916
Not happening.

18:50.379 --> 18:51.045
MOBILE PHONE RECEIPT

18:51.046 --> 18:52.297
14:02
MONDAY, NOVEMBER 2ND

18:57.553 --> 18:59.887
A gymnasium, huh…

18:59.888 --> 19:03.057
Are you just running,
or are you trying to lure me?

19:03.058 --> 19:05.017
I could smoke you out with fire,

19:05.018 --> 19:08.604
but playing tag again sounds like a pain.

19:08.605 --> 19:10.732
So, what will I do?

19:12.484 --> 19:14.611
<i>All right. Just like I pictured it.</i>

19:15.362 --> 19:17.239
<i>It's the perfect size.</i>

19:18.490 --> 19:22.828
What are you plotting, you little brat?

19:23.912 --> 19:26.582
You are the one who has set
something up, aren't you?

19:31.920 --> 19:34.590
Sorcerers live and die by lying.

20:30.729 --> 20:34.523
What I recreate
is basically like <i>shikigami.</i>

20:34.524 --> 20:37.693
So I can give it simple commands.

20:37.694 --> 20:40.614
A kitchen knife doesn't usually
fly around on its own, right?

20:41.490 --> 20:44.325
This is probably pointless with you,

20:44.326 --> 20:45.660
but I'll ask anyway.

20:45.661 --> 20:48.747
If you hand over your points,
I'll make it quick.

20:50.082 --> 20:53.293
Barrier techniques are tough, aren't they?

20:54.544 --> 20:56.254
No matter how long I try,

20:56.255 --> 20:59.257
I can't get a feel for layering

20:59.258 --> 21:01.717
a scaled-down pseudo space
over real space.

21:01.718 --> 21:02.803
So…

21:03.720 --> 21:04.972
<i>Don't tell me…</i>

21:06.682 --> 21:09.518
I'm going to repurpose this gym's space

21:10.018 --> 21:12.646
as my domain.

21:13.230 --> 21:14.564
You can do that?

21:34.751 --> 21:36.336
Domain Expansion.

21:36.920 --> 21:38.297
Chimera Shadow Garden.

21:42.843 --> 21:45.594
DOMAIN EXPANSION
CHIMERA SHADOW GARDEN

21:45.595 --> 21:48.890
So you are already
such an advanced sorcerer…

21:49.683 --> 21:51.475
I never said I didn't have…

21:51.476 --> 21:53.395
a big finishing move.

23:27.280 --> 23:30.157
<i>Even unfinished, a domain’s a domain.</i>

23:30.158 --> 23:31.742
<i>Bring out your "trump card"</i>

23:31.743 --> 23:33.494
<i>- and activate it!
- Not yet.</i>

23:33.495 --> 23:35.246
<i>- Hang in there.
- I’ll give it to you.</i>

23:35.247 --> 23:36.956
<i>Let’s see who breaks first!</i>

23:36.957 --> 23:39.291
<i>Then break already!</i>

23:39.292 --> 23:40.877
NEXT EPISODE
